Design inspiration
------------------

firmeye
  The original firmeye project (DEAD_UPSTREAM) was a firmware reverse
  engineering pipeline. embalmer's pipeline-orchestration framing — extract,
  inspect, analyze, report — is inspired by firmeye's design intent.


Extraction engine
-----------------

unblob  (https://github.com/onekey-sec/unblob)
  Copyright (c) ONEKEY GmbH and contributors.
  Licensed under the MIT License.

  embalmer uses unblob as its recursive extraction backend. embalmer does not
  reimplement extraction; it orchestrates unblob and composes the results with
  filesystem inspection and binary analysis. All firmware extraction is
  performed by unblob and its underlying extractors (sasquatch, jefferson,
  ubi_reader, 7z, and others).


